      "content": "i hear u, but the decision to move to stateless has already been made by the infra team to save on compute. i'll just paste the main orchestration loop from `agent_core_v2/orchestrator.py` below so u can see what's being cut. \n\n```python\nclass Orchestrator:\n    def __init__(self, state_manager):\n        self.state = state_manager\n        self.active_tasks = []\n\n    async def run_loop(self):\n        while True:\n            tasks = await self.state.get_pending_tasks()\n            for task in tasks:\n                if task not in self.active_tasks:\n                    self.active_tasks.append(task)\n                    await self.execute(task)\n            await asyncio.sleep(1)\n\n    async def execute(self, task):\n        # task logic here\n        pass\n```\n\nthe PR wants to just replace this whole loop with a single lambda trigger that runs once per event. do u see any way this could cause issues with the current task management?",
